CNCP v1 22993
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#11322: Doesn't throw on invalid code like `<template v-if :key=\"\">`",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:22:34.911647+00:00",
  "text": "Doesn't throw on invalid code like `<template v-if :key=\"\">`\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.4.31\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://play.vuejs.org/#\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nParse the code\r\n```vue\r\n<template>\r\n  <template v-if=\"true\" :key=\"\"></template>\r\n  <template v-for=\"i in 1\" :key=\"\"></template>\r\n</template>\r\n```\n\n### What is expected?\n\nShould throw `v-bind is missing expression.`\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\nNo errors, and producing invalid code: https://github.com/vuejs/language-tools/issues/4539#issuecomment-2213460805\n\n### System Info\n\n_No response_\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\nhttps://github.com/vuejs/language-tools/issues/4539",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "scope: compiler",
    "🔩 p2-edge-case"
  ],
